commit_list.message:
Changed Version to 0.3.1: Added a bunch of new Superhero armors, continued to work on the powers.

I also tweaked a bunch of the armor textures to look much more like
their model textures, and replaced some ugly weird item textures with
ones I made using the model texture as a reference.
I removed the Batman (the default version) class and references, instead
I'll continue to add the specific costume versions as I go, I didn't
have a single default batman texture to use.
I finally got item textures for the ATOM costume, and so I uncommented
those parts. I commented them because I didn't have the Texture.
I fixed texture registry problems, with Blue Lantern and Star Sapphire
because the filenames were wrong.
I added the following new costume sets:
Antman Classic
ATOM Suit
Doctor Strange
Captain Britain
Baron Zemo
Black Adam
DeadShot
Yellow Lantern
Red Hood
Professor Zoom

I changed the following costume textures:
Deadpool
ATOM
Antman
Booster Gold
Blue Beetle
Dr. Fate
Ms. Marvel
Captain Marvel
Daredevil

I worked on the powers for the Flash and Antman.
The speed increase works, along with being able to run over the incline
without having to jump, and a jump speed increase, but the Antman powers
did not work right, except for being able to jump forward faster like
Antman would. I could not get the player size change/reduction to work
correctly. I checked out the main existing superhero Mod, (which I
love), and it seems that the author used a small sized mob, which the
player rides on instead of actually changing the player's model/size and
bounding box, and then he also used a very large mob (probably a giant
zombie, something which already exists hidden in the Minecraft code
which you can summon using commands) and then have the player become
invisible and riding the huge mob. Also, I think I figured out how he
made the Flash be able to run through buildings, by teleporting the
player to the next open spot on the same level on the Y axis (the same
level/height in the world), and when it's in front of the player. It
also seems to limit the player's speed increase to using the "W"
key/going forward, so the player can still control movement side to side
and maneuver into side streets and such. I haven't figured out how I
could do that yet, but it should be possible. I need to work on learning
about keyBindings and event handling more and then utilizing them much
more for the powers. I need to create a set of standard, custom effects,
such as "Magic", "Super-Strength", "Flight", "Invulnerability",
"Teleportation", "Agility", "Speed Force", "Wall Climbing",
"Weather-Control" and more. Then I can implement those generic effects
in each superhero that they apply to, instead of having to figure out
each of the specific things that are needed for that effect, and adding
them individually to each hero they affect. Then, I can customize them
if necessary within that hero's Armor class, but that would be a small
change just for that hero.
